io.phrasefinder

Class PhraseFinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.phrasefinder.PhraseFinder

  • public final class PhraseFinder
extends java.lang.Object
    Class PhraseFinder provides routines for querying the PhraseFinder web service. Class Demo.java shows a usage example.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  PhraseFinder.Corpus

      static class  PhraseFinder.Options
      Options represents optional parameters that can be sent along with a query.
      static class  PhraseFinder.Phrase
      Phrase represents a phrase, also called n-gram.
      static class  PhraseFinder.Result
      Result represents a search result.
      static class  PhraseFinder.Status
      Status is a type that reports whether a request was successful or not.
      static class  PhraseFinder.Token
      Token represents a single token (word, punctuation mark, etc.) as part of a phrase.

    • Method Detail

      • search

        public static PhraseFinder.Result search(java.lang.String query)
                                  throws java.io.IOException
        Sends a request to the server with all optional parameters set to default.
        Parameters:
        query - is the query string.
        Returns:
        A PhraseFinder.Result object whose PhraseFinder.Result.status field is equal to PhraseFinder.Status.OK if the request was successful. In this case other fields of the object are in valid state and can be read. Any status other than PhraseFinder.Status.OK indicates a failed request. In that case other fields in the result have unspecified data.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - when sending the request or receiving the response failed.

        Parameters:

        options - are the parameters.

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Same as search(String)
